{
  "_comment": [
    "Seccomp profile for codeflow-sandbox-controller (sc-538 / epic 526).",
    "",
    "Default action is SCMP_ACT_ERRNO — any syscall not on the allowlist below",
    "returns EPERM. The allowlist is the conservative set a Go static binary",
    "running an HTTPS server and dialing one unix socket actually needs.",
    "",
    "Specifically denied (because they are NOT on the allowlist):",
    "  mount, umount, umount2, pivot_root, chroot, swapon, swapoff",
    "  init_module, finit_module, delete_module, kexec_load, kexec_file_load",
    "  bpf, perf_event_open, ptrace, process_vm_readv, process_vm_writev",
    "  keyctl, add_key, request_key",
    "  reboot, settimeofday, clock_settime, adjtimex, clock_adjtime",
    "  iopl, ioperm",
    "  setdomainname, sethostname",
    "  unshare (the controller never creates new namespaces — dockerd does that)",
    "  setns (same)",
    "  acct, vhangup, quotactl, nfsservctl",
    "  create_module, query_module, get_kernel_syms",
    "  mbind, migrate_pages, move_pages, set_mempolicy",
    "  sysfs, syslog (read access via /proc; the syscall is blocked)",
    "",
    "How to verify in CI / staging:",
    "  1) Run the container with this profile loaded.",
    "  2) Exercise the API end-to-end (controller scaffold tests).",
    "  3) Check audit log for SECCOMP audit records — none should appear.",
    "",
    "Updating the profile:",
    "  When sc-529 wires real docker-API calls or sc-534 adds OTLP, new",
    "  syscalls may be needed. Add them here with a brief inline note above",
    "  the syscall name. Do not add to the deny list above without updating",
    "  the rationale here too.",
    "",
    "Reference: docker default profile at",
    "  https://github.com/moby/moby/blob/master/profiles/seccomp/default.json"
  ],
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "archMap": [
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_X86", "SCMP_ARCH_X32"]
    },
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_ARM"]
    }
  ],
